1
00:00:28,928 --> 00:00:31,200
♪In cool weather♪

2
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,312
♪I fly over the sea to see you♪

3
00:00:33,536 --> 00:00:37,611
♪As fast as I can♪

4
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,384
♪I don't know why♪

5
00:00:40,384 --> 00:00:42,624
♪But I've had my heart set on it♪

6
00:00:42,624 --> 00:00:46,890
♪I've been eager to meet you♪

7
00:00:47,224 --> 00:00:49,472
♪I keep practicing with trembling hands♪

8
00:00:49,472 --> 00:00:51,712
♪Learning to embrace you♪

9
00:00:51,712 --> 00:00:55,808
♪The brilliant roses are withering♪

10
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,688
♪Sunshine is sprinkled on the earth♪

11
00:00:58,688 --> 00:01:00,896
♪Passing through
the splendid four seasons♪

12
00:01:00,896 --> 00:01:05,504
♪I must see you♪

13
00:01:05,504 --> 00:01:09,952
♪I will see you at any cost♪

14
00:01:09,952 --> 00:01:14,592
♪While I am young♪

15
00:01:14,592 --> 00:01:16,928
♪I will hold you tightly♪

16
00:01:16,928 --> 00:01:19,200
♪And tell you♪

17
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:23,776
♪How important you are to me♪

18
00:01:23,776 --> 00:01:28,352
♪I will see you at any cost♪

19
00:01:28,352 --> 00:01:32,896
♪Whatever we said when parting♪

20
00:01:32,896 --> 00:01:37,792
♪No matter how far apart we may be♪

21
00:01:37,792 --> 00:01:41,794
♪I will grasp your hands♪

22
00:01:41,794 --> 00:01:44,672
♪And take you with me♪

23
00:01:44,672 --> 00:01:46,528
=Sweet Games =

24
00:01:49,895 --> 00:01:51,135
(We often use a hundred reasons)

25
00:01:51,135 --> 00:01:52,415
(why we can't be together)

26
00:01:52,975 --> 00:01:54,695
(to fight against
that moment of heart flip.)

27
00:01:56,335 --> 00:01:57,855
(Yet we forget that love itself)

28
00:01:57,855 --> 00:01:59,535
(is about following the inner voice.)

29
00:02:00,255 --> 00:02:02,775
It's like Darcy
chasing Elizabeth in the rain,

30
00:02:04,326 --> 00:02:06,806
(telling her those three words,
"I love you.")

31
00:02:07,766 --> 00:02:10,366
(He plucked up the courage to pour out)

32
00:02:10,606 --> 00:02:11,846
(the overflowing love in his heart.)

33
00:02:12,366 --> 00:02:15,366
No matter what the outcome,
I have to tell you,

34
00:02:16,366 --> 00:02:18,846
("You are the one for me.")

35
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:28,944
=Episode 10=
(Let's Be Together Then)

36
00:02:30,686 --> 00:02:31,806
I really didn't expect

37
00:02:32,126 --> 00:02:34,566
that someone would say
our game is not sweet enough.

38
00:02:34,806 --> 00:02:35,806
No way.

39
00:02:35,806 --> 00:02:38,126
It's not sweet?
I'm nearly choked by the sweetness.

40
00:02:38,646 --> 00:02:40,646
I think the players' doubts make sense.

41
00:02:40,926 --> 00:02:44,486
After all, looking around,
there's a room full of singles.

42
00:02:45,046 --> 00:02:45,966
So pitiful.

43
00:02:46,366 --> 00:02:48,486
Who are you calling pitiful?
You're not pitiful?

44
00:02:48,966 --> 00:02:51,766
You're pitiful.
Can you be on par with me?

45
00:02:52,326 --> 00:02:53,886
Mr. Hu, Mr. Hu.

46
00:02:54,046 --> 00:02:56,566
You see, our work

47
00:02:56,566 --> 00:02:59,406
is almost done. We only have to
wait for the favorable rate now.

48
00:03:00,006 --> 00:03:02,806
What about letting us go back and rest?

49
00:03:05,606 --> 00:03:06,766
Changfeng is right.

50
00:03:08,366 --> 00:03:10,966
You have been working hard indeed.

51
00:03:10,966 --> 00:03:14,046
Now, put down your work
and hurry back home.

52
00:03:14,046 --> 00:03:14,926
- Weekend...
- Thank you, boss.

53
00:03:14,926 --> 00:03:16,966
- I haven't done my words.
- Thank you, boss.

54
00:03:17,366 --> 00:03:19,926
- Wu.
- Sorry. Wait for me.

55
00:03:33,486 --> 00:03:34,606
Why are you sitting here?

56
00:03:36,366 --> 00:03:38,046
Everyone has been hardworking recently.

57
00:03:38,366 --> 00:03:39,766
So, I let them go.

58
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:42,166
The weekend starts now.

59
00:03:42,486 --> 00:03:44,326
As for the favorable rate,
let's leave it to fate.

60
00:03:44,966 --> 00:03:46,046
Then why haven't you left yet?

61
00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:51,766
I was thinking of
having Miss An buy me a drink.

62
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:55,046
Let's go. My treat.

63
00:03:55,366 --> 00:03:58,046
So straightforward? Let's go.

64
00:04:03,886 --> 00:04:06,206
The last time you treated me...

65
00:04:06,606 --> 00:04:07,766
It was the last time.

66
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,886
Well said. Such nonsense.

67
00:04:13,166 --> 00:04:14,166
Was it that time

68
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:15,446
when you cheated me into investing?

69
00:04:16,886 --> 00:04:18,366
No. I paid that time too.

70
00:04:18,526 --> 00:04:21,646
- It doesn't matter. Come on.
- Cheers.

71
00:04:28,126 --> 00:04:29,006
Where are you two now?

72
00:04:29,006 --> 00:04:30,126
Hurry up.

73
00:04:41,646 --> 00:04:42,486
Miser An,

74
00:04:44,086 --> 00:04:44,966
tell me,

75
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:47,486
why did we have to choose to
start a business back then?

76
00:04:48,766 --> 00:04:51,046
If you hadn't broken up with that one,

77
00:04:51,446 --> 00:04:52,646
wouldn't a rich lady life

78
00:04:52,646 --> 00:04:53,766
be pretty comfortable?

79
00:04:54,366 --> 00:04:56,206
Then why didn't you choose

80
00:04:56,206 --> 00:04:57,646
the most comfortable path?

81
00:04:59,206 --> 00:05:00,326
No one can tell.

82
00:05:01,286 --> 00:05:01,966
Cheers.

83
00:05:07,486 --> 00:05:08,606
Tell me,

84
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:10,886
can we make it this time?

85
00:05:13,766 --> 00:05:16,486
Luck is what happens
when preparation meets opportunity.

86
00:05:18,526 --> 00:05:19,806
I think

87
00:05:19,806 --> 00:05:22,886
we've been really tough these years.

88
00:05:23,726 --> 00:05:24,846
But being able to

89
00:05:25,326 --> 00:05:28,166
continue this journey with you all,

90
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:29,406
I feel

91
00:05:31,886 --> 00:05:33,446
pretty good.

92
00:05:34,286 --> 00:05:37,366
I'm very happy and at ease.

93
00:05:39,286 --> 00:05:41,326
If this time we really
make Gaishi Unparalleled big,

94
00:05:41,606 --> 00:05:42,486
what are your plans?

95
00:05:43,206 --> 00:05:45,286
I have nothing. What plan could I have?

96
00:05:45,286 --> 00:05:46,406
Think about it. Think about it.

97
00:05:46,686 --> 00:05:48,446
I just think

98
00:05:49,806 --> 00:05:51,926
I hope I can

99
00:05:52,726 --> 00:05:55,006
face everything in life

100
00:05:55,206 --> 00:05:59,886
with ease and happiness.

101
00:06:01,526 --> 00:06:03,406
So you don't plan
to start a romantic relationship?

102
00:06:09,046 --> 00:06:12,406
Miser An, so happy that you are asleep?

103
00:06:22,926 --> 00:06:25,006
Timi.

104
00:06:30,326 --> 00:06:35,286
Hu Yingjun, why did you drink so much?

105
00:06:37,846 --> 00:06:41,086
An Ran, An Ran.

106
00:06:56,406 --> 00:06:58,006
Cheerful.

107
00:07:05,966 --> 00:07:06,806
Leave her alone.

108
00:07:06,806 --> 00:07:08,806
Let's continue it later.
I'll finish this game soon.

109
00:07:14,246 --> 00:07:15,686
An Ran, we're going home.

110
00:07:18,246 --> 00:07:19,206
Let's go, An Ran.

111
00:07:24,246 --> 00:07:26,126
- Watch the stair.
- Leaving?

112
00:07:28,246 --> 00:07:30,806
An Ran, what is...

113
00:07:31,326 --> 00:07:33,206
- She's drunk.
- So soon?

114
00:07:33,646 --> 00:07:35,646
Didn't we agree on
a happy four-person gathering?

115
00:07:35,686 --> 00:07:37,246
Your combat power isn't up to par.

116
00:07:37,246 --> 00:07:38,246
Who are you talking about?

117
00:07:38,246 --> 00:07:39,366
You're the one not up to par.

118
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:40,806
You let An Ran drink so much.

119
00:07:41,126 --> 00:07:42,806
You guys continue.
I'll take her home first.

120
00:07:42,806 --> 00:07:44,766
- Make sure you get her home safely.
- Okay.

121
00:07:45,566 --> 00:07:48,806
- Be careful.
- Bye.

122
00:07:50,766 --> 00:07:52,326
Come on, continue.

123
00:07:52,326 --> 00:07:55,006
Come on. Why are you so late?

124
00:07:55,086 --> 00:07:56,326
You didn't arrive until one of us left.

125
00:07:56,486 --> 00:07:58,126
As An Ran is a light drinker,

126
00:07:58,126 --> 00:08:00,086
and you kept drinking with her,
how could she not get drunk?

127
00:08:00,126 --> 00:08:01,446
What? You want to take revenge for her?

128
00:08:01,446 --> 00:08:03,806
Go on. Stop talking nonsense.

129
00:08:15,886 --> 00:08:16,326
Cheers.

130
00:08:20,006 --> 00:08:21,446
One, two, three, four. At least four.

131
00:08:24,486 --> 00:08:25,246
Come on.

132
00:08:32,886 --> 00:08:34,366
We arrived. At the doorstep.

133
00:08:35,486 --> 00:08:36,766
So sleepy.

134
00:08:43,886 --> 00:08:45,326
Why can't I open it?

135
00:08:45,486 --> 00:08:46,646
This is my home.

136
00:08:46,886 --> 00:08:48,766
This isn't my home?

137
00:08:49,526 --> 00:08:51,566
This is your home.

138
00:08:52,126 --> 00:08:54,006
That's my home, right?

139
00:09:08,806 --> 00:09:11,246
Come on. I haven't fallen yet.

140
00:09:14,126 --> 00:09:16,006
I've always been curious.

141
00:09:17,246 --> 00:09:19,246
For someone like you
who are born with a silver spoon

142
00:09:19,886 --> 00:09:21,566
and work by fits and starts,

143
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:25,126
why are you willing to
work with An Ran until now?

144
00:09:25,926 --> 00:09:27,366
Can I be the same as them?

145
00:09:35,886 --> 00:09:39,006
Do you see it? The scar on my eyebrow.

146
00:09:44,326 --> 00:09:45,686
It's quite deep.

147
00:09:46,246 --> 00:09:47,566
I never noticed it before.

148
00:09:48,126 --> 00:09:52,126
How about it?
Is a man more handsome with a scar?

149
00:09:58,206 --> 00:10:02,126
Listen, An Ran and I
are childhood friends.

150
00:10:02,446 --> 00:10:05,806
As you know,
I am tall, handsome, and fair now.

151
00:10:06,686 --> 00:10:10,686
Why are you laughing?
Am I not tall, handsome, or fair?

152
00:10:11,006 --> 00:10:12,006
You

153
00:10:12,446 --> 00:10:14,006
are just tall.

154
00:10:15,566 --> 00:10:18,566
But back then, I was just that tall.

155
00:10:19,566 --> 00:10:21,886
Look at An Ran's height now.

156
00:10:22,126 --> 00:10:24,326
Back then, she was
actually taller than me.

157
00:10:25,126 --> 00:10:26,326
We were both naughty.

158
00:10:26,686 --> 00:10:29,806
Naughty kids are prone to getting hurt.

159
00:10:30,446 --> 00:10:31,806
This is a remnant from that time.

160
00:10:32,246 --> 00:10:34,246
We were bullied
by the older kids in the alley.

161
00:10:35,886 --> 00:10:36,886
I couldn't beat them down.

162
00:10:38,126 --> 00:10:39,566
But An Ran stood up for me.

163
00:10:42,566 --> 00:10:43,886
Even if she couldn't win,
she would still fight.

164
00:10:46,086 --> 00:10:48,206
I can imagine what she looked like.

165
00:10:51,566 --> 00:10:52,806
In my heart at that time,

166
00:10:56,246 --> 00:10:57,686
An Ran was like Ultraman.

167
00:11:07,566 --> 00:11:09,126
Of course I have a way out.

168
00:11:11,886 --> 00:11:13,126
I can always go home
and live comfortably,

169
00:11:13,126 --> 00:11:14,126
being a rich kid, right?

170
00:11:15,246 --> 00:11:16,246
But An Ran can't.

171
00:11:18,006 --> 00:11:18,886
She has no way out.

172
00:11:21,246 --> 00:11:22,446
So I have to stand by her.

173
00:11:24,006 --> 00:11:25,126
I must support her.

174
00:11:35,246 --> 00:11:37,326
- What about you?
- What about me?

175
00:11:37,686 --> 00:11:38,886
Why did you come to Gaishi Unparalleled?

176
00:11:41,566 --> 00:11:43,126
Of course it's because of An Ran.

177
00:11:43,686 --> 00:11:45,446
An Ran asked me to help her.

178
00:11:45,446 --> 00:11:46,686
How could I possibly not come?

179
00:11:49,126 --> 00:11:50,086
I'll show you

180
00:11:50,086 --> 00:11:51,446
my photo when I was in school

181
00:11:51,446 --> 00:11:53,566
before I went abroad.
Do you want to see it?

182
00:11:58,126 --> 00:12:00,086
Is it completely

183
00:12:00,246 --> 00:12:02,566
different from now?

184
00:12:03,246 --> 00:12:05,966
You were so good-looking back then.

185
00:12:06,206 --> 00:12:08,006
How did you end up like this?

186
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:11,126
Back then, I was highly shortsighted,

187
00:12:11,446 --> 00:12:12,486
so I wore glasses,

188
00:12:12,886 --> 00:12:14,446
(and I didn't know how to dress up.)

189
00:12:15,446 --> 00:12:17,926
(I lacked confidence in everything.)

190
00:12:18,086 --> 00:12:19,646
(I was always ready to give up.)

191
00:12:38,766 --> 00:12:41,086
Hello, do you need me?

192
00:12:42,126 --> 00:12:45,566
I-I saw your painting

193
00:12:46,006 --> 00:12:48,006
at the exhibition.

194
00:12:48,326 --> 00:12:49,686
I thought it was excellent.

195
00:12:50,246 --> 00:12:53,686
I've always failed to find
a student who paints in this style,

196
00:12:54,326 --> 00:12:56,446
so I wanted to learn about

197
00:12:57,006 --> 00:12:58,446
how you learned it.

198
00:12:58,886 --> 00:13:00,326
You like my painting?

199
00:13:01,126 --> 00:13:02,006
Thank you.

200
00:13:02,446 --> 00:13:03,566
What's your name?

201
00:13:04,886 --> 00:13:08,246
My name is Bai Mengyao.

202
00:13:09,886 --> 00:13:11,446
So you are Bai Mengyao?

203
00:13:11,886 --> 00:13:13,446
I also really like your paintings.

204
00:13:14,326 --> 00:13:15,246
Really?

205
00:13:15,446 --> 00:13:16,566
Among the row at the exhibition,

206
00:13:16,566 --> 00:13:18,126
your painting was the first I noticed.

207
00:13:18,366 --> 00:13:20,366
You could produce such a personal style

208
00:13:20,366 --> 00:13:22,246
just in your first year.

209
00:13:22,246 --> 00:13:24,006
Your talent is really strong.

210
00:13:24,326 --> 00:13:25,206
Thank you.

211
00:13:25,926 --> 00:13:28,366
(I didn't expect
to hit it off with An Ran)

212
00:13:28,886 --> 00:13:30,086
(and become friends with her.)

213
00:13:31,566 --> 00:13:34,486
(Back then, we often drew together.)

214
00:13:42,006 --> 00:13:44,886
Mengyao, Mengyao, here.

215
00:13:47,446 --> 00:13:48,806
I wasted all this.

216
00:13:49,446 --> 00:13:51,326
This brand of paint is expensive.

217
00:13:54,006 --> 00:13:54,446
Here.

218
00:13:54,806 --> 00:13:55,566
Use mine.

219
00:13:57,446 --> 00:13:58,246
Thank you, Ran.

220
00:13:58,566 --> 00:14:00,686
I'll return it to you
when I buy the same one as yours.

221
00:14:01,126 --> 00:14:02,246
It's just a tube of paint.

222
00:14:02,246 --> 00:14:03,446
Why are you so formal?

223
00:14:12,446 --> 00:14:13,126
Ran,

224
00:14:13,446 --> 00:14:14,446
actually,

225
00:14:14,566 --> 00:14:16,686
I received the admission letter
from a French school

226
00:14:16,686 --> 00:14:17,926
yesterday.

227
00:14:18,246 --> 00:14:19,126
Really?

228
00:14:19,686 --> 00:14:20,566
That's great!

229
00:14:22,806 --> 00:14:25,806
But why do you look so gloomy?

230
00:14:26,566 --> 00:14:28,566
Isn't that school your dream school?

231
00:14:30,886 --> 00:14:33,566
I-I may not be able to go.

232
00:14:34,006 --> 00:14:38,446
- Why?
- I didn't get a scholarship.

233
00:14:44,686 --> 00:14:47,446
So how much are you short now?

234
00:14:50,126 --> 00:14:52,806
My family helped me put together some,

235
00:14:53,686 --> 00:14:56,806
and I saved some these years,

236
00:14:57,366 --> 00:14:58,806
but I'm still tens of thousands short.

237
00:15:02,126 --> 00:15:03,886
I see. I've saved fifty thousand.

238
00:15:04,006 --> 00:15:05,086
Take it, alright?

239
00:15:06,806 --> 00:15:09,846
Ran, where did you get so much money?

240
00:15:10,806 --> 00:15:12,126
From previous competitions,

241
00:15:12,366 --> 00:15:14,206
and selling paintings.

242
00:15:14,606 --> 00:15:16,366
Not much. Just fifty thousand.

243
00:15:16,886 --> 00:15:18,126
I hope it can help you.

244
00:15:18,806 --> 00:15:19,806
No, no.

245
00:15:20,606 --> 00:15:22,486
How can I take your money?

246
00:15:22,486 --> 00:15:24,086
And you're about to graduate.

247
00:15:24,246 --> 00:15:25,886
What if you have an emergency?

248
00:15:27,606 --> 00:15:32,126
Forget it. As it's not mine,

249
00:15:33,006 --> 00:15:34,006
there's no use thinking about it.

250
00:15:34,886 --> 00:15:37,246
I won't think about it. I won't go.

251
00:15:42,446 --> 00:15:44,366
Mengyao, listen to me.

252
00:15:44,726 --> 00:15:46,886
Haven't you always dreamed of becoming

253
00:15:46,886 --> 00:15:47,966
a great painter?

254
00:15:49,206 --> 00:15:50,886
I think this trip to France

255
00:15:50,886 --> 00:15:52,846
is a very, very good opportunity.

256
00:15:53,246 --> 00:15:54,566
You're so talented.

257
00:15:54,686 --> 00:15:56,486
You can definitely progress soon.

258
00:15:57,366 --> 00:16:00,486
If you give up
due to a little difficulty,

259
00:16:00,966 --> 00:16:02,206
that would be a pity.

260
00:16:04,566 --> 00:16:07,806
But dreams are expensive.

261
00:16:09,206 --> 00:16:13,326
Someone like me can't afford it.

262
00:16:16,446 --> 00:16:18,606
Dreams indeed are expensive,

263
00:16:20,366 --> 00:16:21,366
but they're also worth it.

264
00:16:23,126 --> 00:16:26,006
You are worth it too.

265
00:16:30,206 --> 00:16:31,246
Is that true, Ran?

266
00:16:36,126 --> 00:16:37,086
For the fifty thousand,

267
00:16:37,086 --> 00:16:38,206
you take it first.

268
00:16:38,206 --> 00:16:40,966
I think it should be enough
for half a year's living expenses.

269
00:16:43,606 --> 00:16:46,846
As for tuition, you can
apply for a study abroad loan.

270
00:16:47,086 --> 00:16:48,806
